com.symantec.dlpx.flexresponse

Class ConfiguredPlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.symantec.dlpx.flexresponse.ConfiguredPlugin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IncidentResponseActionFactory, Plugin

    public abstract class ConfiguredPlugin
extends java.lang.Object
implements Plugin
    When you want to write a plugin that received configuration parameters when it is constructed, you can make use of this class. To do so, simply extend this class,and then the Java compiler will force you to write the correct constructor. You can alternately just write a class with a constructor with the same parameters as the ConfiguredPlugin constructor, without extending this class. At runtime, the plugin invocation framework will detect that your plugin has this constructor and invoke it. When your constructor takes configuration parameters, you can use this information to set up your plugin. For example, your plugin configuration may specify the number of threads to be used in a thread pool. In your constructor you can initialize your thread pool using this information.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ConfiguredPlugin

        public ConfiguredPlugin(ConfigurationParameters parameters)
        Parameters:
        parameters - The configuration parameters for this plugin. These parameters are defined in the properties file for this plugin. Note that only parameters that are available at system startup will be provided. For example, stored credentials will not be provided at this time, and are only available to the action at the time it is invoked.
